      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey im lookin at a 2018 camry throwin a p0171 code. checked the maf sensor and it seems fine, so i dont think the air intake measurement is the issue. what else should i be lookin at for a lean condition?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A p0171 code in your 2018 Camry, indicating a lean condition, could be due to a few other factors besides the Mass Air Flow (MAF) sensor. You might want to check the oxygen sensor, as it plays a crucial role in maintaining the air-fuel ratio. Also, ensure that the fuel injectors are delivering the correct amount of fuel, and the fuel pressure is adequate. Additionally, inspect the throttle body for any clogs or dirt, as it can affect air intake. Lastly, check the exhaust gas recirculation (EGR) valve, as a malfunctioning EGR valve can cause a lean condition. If you have trouble finding the issue, consider consulting a professional mechanic.",
      "source": "target",
